The paper deals with the optimization of linear precoders and receivers in a multiuser MIMO system, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The use of random matrix theory (RMT) to analyze the system also suggests the statistical learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed transceivers, which could be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SP) category. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of the max-min SINR, which could be relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) category.
